{"id":1643798,"retrievedAt":"2026-02-28T11:39:29.576Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":18,"name":"Drama"}],"homepage":"","id":1643798,"imdb_id":"tt12930540","origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"0.5%","overview":"The streets of Margate are 97% White. Its Black residents, make up just 0.5% of a population of 65,000.  Inspired by award-winning artist Barbara Walker’s Turner Contemporary exhibition 'Place, Space and Who' exploring the lives of marginalised Black women in Margate, 0.5% looks at excerpts of the lives of Black people thriving and surviving in a community, and the fleeting but powerful connection between them.  On a single day in Margate, the sheer existence of four strangers brings joy and comfort to a group of individuals living in the area, and their experiences interlink: Jide, an 81-year-old man who has called Kent home for the last sixty years. Falle, a young father and musician. Kanndiss, who practices self-care through movement. And lastly teenage Shianna, who wonders what lies beyond her small town.","popularity":0.0071,"poster_path":"/2sQocIksnyEkizf8Vmmm5M4MNo6.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":12935,"logo_path":"/rml1bBbFJ33HE0rTrkNpuFVfpAQ.png","name":"BBC Arts","origin_country":"GB"},{"id":102211,"logo_path":"/2etW1NbNcEzX9CB0aA2xztIECPK.png","name":"Screen South","origin_country":"GB"}],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"GB","name":"United Kingdom"}],"release_date":"2022-03-06","revenue":0,"runtime":5,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"English","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English"},{"english_name":"Fulah","iso_639_1":"ff","name":"Fulfulde"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"0.5%","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":6036918,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Falle Nioke","original_name":"Falle Nioke","popularity":0,"profile_path":nul